been offended and some have quit.  The latest<br>
round seems to be centered around &quot;Book Clubs&quot;,<br>
though it sounds like that hopefully has been<br>
cleared up as the simple misunderstanding it<br>
was.<br>
<br>
My 2 cp :<br>
It's very easy for people to be offended in an online<br>
environment. Typing just doesn't communicate well<br>
enough and leaves too much for the imagination, I<br>
believe. Unfortunately, it's been my experience that<br>
what gets filled into the gaps by the reader's<br>
imagination is often negative. The other person is<br>
imagined to be mean or rude or whatever, when<br>
the reality is it was just a miscommunication. It's<br>
happened to me in EQ and other online games where<br>
people concluded I was being incredibly rude or<br>
excluding people or whatever. The funny thing is<br>
that I get along with nearly everyone I meet in RL.<br>
At least, people _seem_ to get along with me (starts<br>
looking suspicious).  <br>
<br>
