whole level-based grouping bit is the culprit, I<br>
believe. That's why the uber guilds exist. Takes care<br>
of all the exclusion problems as everyone in the guild<br>
is in the topmost level range and thus can join in<br>
on anything. But, for the non uber level ranges, the<br>
problem remains. It's a lame part of how EQ works<br>
and it has always caused strife and frustration,<br>
in my opinion.<br>
